article.headline: N.C. State 45, Clemson 43
article.story:
GREENSBORO, N.C. (AP) -- Kaayla Chones scored 13 points and had
12 rebounds to lead North Carolina State to a 45-43 win Saturday
over Clemson in the quarterfinals of the Atlantic Coast Conference
Women's Tournament.

Lakeia Stokes led all scorers with 23 points for Clemson (17-11,
7-9). She was the only player to score in double figures for the
Tigers; Julie Talley scored 8 points and Julie Aderhold scored 6.

Rachel Stockdale had 10 points for the Lady Wolfpack (17-13,
8-8) and Alvine Mendeng added 6, hitting 4-of-4 free-throws.

N.C. State shot 27.5 percent from the field for the game,
including 5-of-21 from behind the 3-point line. Clemson fared
little better, shooting 29 percent and hitting 5-of-17 3-pointers.

N.C. State led 21-16 at the half, holding on through four lead
changes in the game for the win even though Clemson outscored the
Lady Wolfpack 27-24 in the second half.

Clemson scored 11 points off turnovers to N.C. State's 10.

N.C. State advanced to Sunday's semifinals against North
Carolina, who beat Virginia 64-45 in another quarterfinal game of
the ACC tournament Saturday.
